The paper deals with image enhancement and denoising, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of graph-based filtering and spectral methods suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). The mention of Krylov subspace and conjugate gradient algorithm also suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
